  "prompt": "What is the best time table for a student of maths and science of class 11th?",
  "response": "Creating an effective timetable for a Class 11 student studying Maths and Science requires a balance between academics, revision, practice, and self-care. Here\u2019s a sample timetable designed for productivity and efficiency:\n\n---\n\n### **Morning Routine**\n- **6:00 \u2013 6:30 AM**: Wake up, freshen up, and drink water.  \n- **6:30 \u2013 7:00 AM**: Light exercise or meditation (to stay active and focused).  \n- **7:00 \u2013 7:30 AM**: Breakfast (healthy and light).  \n\n---\n\n### **Study Session 1 (High Focus)**  \n- **7:30 \u2013 9:30 AM**: **Mathematics** \u2013 Practice problems (focus on difficult topics).  \n- **9:30 \u2013 10:00 AM**: Short break (relax, stretch, or have a snack).  \n\n---\n\n### **Study Session 2 (Conceptual Learning)**  \n- **10:00 \u2013 12:00 PM**: **Physics** \u2013 Study theory and formulas; solve numerical problems.  \n- **12:00 \u2013 12:30 PM**: Short break (lunch preparation or relaxation).  \n\n---\n\n### **Midday Routine**  \n- **12:30 \u2013 1:30 PM**: Lunch and relaxation (avoid overeating).  \n- **1:30 \u2013 2:00 PM**: Short nap (optional) or light reading.  \n\n---\n\n### **Study Session 3 (Application-Based)**  \n- **2:00 \u2013 4:00 PM**: **Chemistry** \u2013 Focus on reactions, equations, and numericals.  \n- **4:00 \u2013 4:30 PM**: Break (tea/snack, light walk).  \n\n---\n\n### **Study Session 4 (Revision and Practice)**  \n- **4:30 \u2013 6:30 PM**: **Mathematics** \u2013 Revise concepts and solve previous year questions.  \n- **6:30 \u2013 7:00 PM**: Break (relax or chat with family).  \n\n---\n\n- **7:00 \u2013 8:00 PM**: Dinner and family time.  \n\n---\n\n### **Evening Study Session**  \n- **8:00 \u2013 9:30 PM**: **Biology/Physics Chemistry** (Alternate daily) \u2013 Revise notes and solve MCQs.  \n- **9:30 \u2013 10:00 PM**: Wind down (listen to music, read, or meditate).  \n\n---\n\n### **Night Routine**  \n- **10:00 \u2013 10:30 PM**: Light revision or planning for the next day.  \n- **10:30 \u2013 11:00 PM**: Sleep (aim for 7-8 hours of rest).  \n\n---\n\n### Additional Tips:  \n1. **Weekly Planning**: Dedicate weekends to revising the week\u2019s topics, taking mock tests, or focusing on weak areas.  \n2. **Practice**: Solve at least 20-30 problems daily in Maths and Science subjects.  \n3. **Consistency**: Stick to the timetable but remain flexible for adjustments if needed.  \n4. **Self-Care**: Take breaks, stay hydrated, and get enough sleep to avoid burnout.  \n\nThis timetable ensures a balanced approach to learning, practice, and rest, which is essential for Class 11 students.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
